<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-055-288 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 474 909</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE on andamp; about ATandamp;T  Sept 23, 1991 v6 n165 p28(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ATandamp;T-NCR: NCR andamp; ATandamp;T file articles on merger; deal is nowcomplete.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   NCR Corp. (Acquisitions, mergers, divestments)American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (Acquisitions, mergers,divestments).andO;Ticker:    NCR; T.andO;Topic:     MergerTelephone companiesComputer industry.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NCR and ATandamp;T announced that they completed the merger of the two companies at9:35 a.m.andP;  EDT, Thursday, September 19 by filing articles of merger with theMaryland State Department of Assessments and Taxation.andM;NCR also announced that the final certified vote on the merger at the Sept.andO;13, 1991, meeting of NCR shareholders was 53,459,179 shares in favor, or 82.3percent of the total outstanding shares.andP;  A two-thirds vote was required forapproval of the merger.andM;Within five business days of the September 19 closing, the First NationalBank of Boston will send letters of transmittal to NCR shareholdersexplaining how to exchange their NCR certificates for ATandamp;T shares.andP;  Inmerging with NCR, ATandamp;T will issue 184.5 million shares.andM;In accordance with the merger agreement, NCR's board of directors redeemedthe &quot;poison pill&quot; preferred share rights as of Sept. 18.andP;  Within the next twoweeks, NCR shareholders of record on Sept. 18 will receive notice of theredemption and a payment of 5 cents per share.andM;In another merger-related transaction, the Capital Group completed itspurchase of 6.3 million shares of NCR stock on Sept. 18.andP;  With the merger,these shares were converted automatically into 17.9 million shares of ATandamp;Tstock.andM;September 19 marks the last day that NCR stock will trade publicly.andP;  Thestock symbol &quot;NCR,&quot; familiar to tapewatchers since 1965, will disappear fromthe Big Board at the close of trading.andP;  NCR stock has been trading on the NewYork Stock Exchange since the 107-year-old company went public in 1926.andM;Both companies said they were pleased that the merger had been completed andthat they were now positioned to take a leadership role in global networkedcomputing.andO;</TEXT></DOC>